President Barack Obama has proclaimed April 9th as National Former Prisoner of War Recognition Day. The proclamation honors the men and women of the United States Armed Forces who have faced challenges and sacrificed while defending the country's liberties. It pays tribute to the American prisoners of war who endured unimaginable hardship at the hands of foreign captors, highlighting their bravery and selfless service. The proclamation also acknowledges the families and friends of these service members who have supported them and borne their own burdens. President Obama calls upon all Americans, as well as government officials and organizations, to observe this day of remembrance and honor our service members, veterans, and all American prisoners of war.